special place because this church

00:02:14.700 --> 00:02:21.000
in this site, in this area have
been tied to the history and life

00:02:21.000 --> 00:02:25.000
of African-Americans
since the early 1800s.

00:02:35.100 --> 00:02:36.400
Thank you.

00:02:39.280 --> 00:02:47.430 position:56%
This tragedy reminds us of the price
so many have had to pay for freedom.

00:02:47.430 --> 00:02:50.590
For all the freedom
is a universal right.

00:02:50.590 --> 00:02:54.740
It is not always recognized
as such and we should never,

00:02:54.740 --> 00:02:57.880
never take freedom for granted.

00:02:57.880 --> 00:03:01.620
There are still today an
estimated 30 million people

00:03:01.620 --> 00:03:08.070
who are illegally enslaved in
Asia, Latin America, and Africa.

00:03:08.070 --> 00:03:12.500
What is important is to remember
that freedom is not only a matter

00:03:12.500 --> 00:03:17.340
of physical freedom i.e. to be able
to live where one wants to live,

00:03:17.340 --> 00:03:22.580
to travel wherever one desires, to
choose how to earn one's living.

00:03:22.580 --> 00:03:27.350
But it is also the freedom
to say what one thinks,

00:03:27.350 --> 00:03:34.420
the freedom to follow one's
faith, the freedom to read, write,

00:03:34.420 --> 00:03:41.670
create in a way that
is unhindered and free.

00:03:41.670 --> 00:03:46.500
In many parts of the world, people
are killed for their beliefs,

00:03:46.500 --> 00:03:51.820
imprisoned for their writings,
flogged for their blogs,

00:03:51.820 --> 00:03:55.250
beheaded for their views.

00:03:55.250 --> 00:04:01.120
So today, we should remember all
those who gave their lives to fight

00:04:01.120 --> 00:04:09.340
for those freedoms and again, we
should not ever rest on our laurels

00:04:09.340 --> 00:04:12.630 position:56%
and believe that freedom is a given.

00:04:12.630 --> 00:04:16.910
We should always in every
way defend those rights,

00:04:16.910 --> 00:04:22.610
speak up against attempts to limit
or to curtail them in any way.

00:04:22.610 --> 00:04:27.030
And today, we have you here.

00:04:27.030 --> 00:04:33.510
We have you here to speak to us
of black literature and literacy.

00:04:33.510 --> 00:04:42.270
Of this important, incredibly
important issue of the right

00:04:42.270 --> 00:04:47.140
to speak up, to write, to
think freely, to create

00:04:47.140 --> 00:04:49.970
and to share with others.

