02:18:59.110 --> 02:19:02.830
One of my very next jobs was
working for Martha's Table.

02:19:02.830 --> 02:19:04.430
I lived above Martha's Table.

02:19:04.430 --> 02:19:05.730
There's an apartment there.

02:19:05.730 --> 02:19:07.030
I don't know if you're
familiar with it.

02:19:07.030 --> 02:19:08.330
It's on 14th and W Street.

02:19:08.330 --> 02:19:09.630
It's basically a soup kitchen.

02:19:09.630 --> 02:19:11.460
I lived above it as an employee.

02:19:11.460 --> 02:19:12.760
One of the most amazing things

02:19:12.760 --> 02:19:16.140
that I saw while living there
was gentrification in action.

02:19:16.140 --> 02:19:18.660
It was something that
I was able to take

02:19:18.660 --> 02:19:20.630
to the prison system
when I talked there.

02:19:20.630 --> 02:19:23.070
Fourteenth and W Street
is notorious.

02:19:23.070 --> 02:19:24.370
What is notorious?

02:19:24.370 --> 02:19:25.670
Eighties and '90s.

02:19:25.670 --> 02:19:26.970
I joke with people all the time.

02:19:26.970 --> 02:19:28.910
If you got caught at 14th
and Clifton, 14th and W,

02:19:28.910 --> 02:19:30.210
you call somebody to come get you.

02:19:30.210 --> 02:19:32.780
They'd tell you to walk a couple
blocks south before they came get

02:19:32.780 --> 02:19:34.080
you, right [laughter]?

02:19:34.080 --> 02:19:36.890
So I'm living above
Martha's Table, 2003 I think,

02:19:36.890 --> 02:19:39.620
before they broke ground for
what is now Busboys and Poets.

02:19:39.620 --> 02:19:43.090
Once again, the corner's notorious.

02:19:43.090 --> 02:19:45.170
You know the signs
of gentrification.

02:19:45.170 --> 02:19:48.420
First you start seeing
homosexual couples

02:19:48.420 --> 02:19:51.520
because they've been ostracized
from the rest of their community

02:19:51.520 --> 02:19:53.890
and so they come to the place
where they can buy stuff.

02:19:53.890 --> 02:19:55.400
Then this is what happens next.

02:19:55.400 --> 02:19:57.320
I saw it right on my corner.

02:19:57.320 --> 02:20:02.150 position:56%
They brought in the National Guard
with [inaudible] and M16s and camped

02:20:02.150 --> 02:20:04.920
out on the corner for a month.

02:20:04.920 --> 02:20:06.680
Right? During that month they shut

02:20:06.680 --> 02:20:09.190
down whatever illegal
operation was going on.

02:20:09.190 --> 02:20:12.550
Then they brought in the
developers and broke ground, right?

02:20:12.550 --> 02:20:14.290
I saw the process happen
out of my window,

02:20:14.290 --> 02:20:20.050 position:56%
and what blew me away the most was
that as notorious as 14th and W was,

02:20:20.050 --> 02:20:23.240
the government, the politicians,
the military, the police,

02:20:23.240 --> 02:20:25.550
could have shut it
down at any moment --

02:20:25.550 --> 02:20:28.100
during the '80s, during the '90s,
when it was dangerous there.

02:20:28.100 --> 02:20:29.650
They could have shut
it down at any moment.

02:20:29.650 --> 02:20:31.620
They waited until they
realized there was a point

02:20:31.620 --> 02:20:33.810
when it was valuable to them,
and then, all of a sudden,

02:20:33.810 --> 02:20:35.690
all the crime stopped
immediately [finger snap].

02:20:35.690 --> 02:20:38.120
Then the next stage
of gentrification,

02:20:38.120 --> 02:20:41.040
when you see whites going
jogging with their dogs at 11 p.m.

02:20:41.040 --> 02:20:53.150
You feel weird about it because
you're like why do they feel safe?

02:20:53.150 --> 02:20:54.470
They shouldn't feel safe.

02:20:54.470 --> 02:20:55.830
They shouldn't feel safe.

02:20:55.830 --> 02:21:00.420
Someone comes -- I'm not the only
one who's been making these things,

02:21:00.420 --> 02:21:01.720
right?

02:21:01.720 --> 02:21:03.020
I've lived this thing and
seen it happening first-hand.

02:21:03.020 --> 02:21:04.320
So when I've walked to these
different prison institutions

02:21:04.320 --> 02:21:05.620
and talked to young people
about writing and about reading,

02:21:05.620 --> 02:21:07.740
the first thing they always say
to me is, "No one understands me.

02:21:07.740 --> 02:21:09.500
No one gets what I'm trying to say.

02:21:09.500 --> 02:21:12.530
No one gets my words, my
feelings, my emotions."

02:21:12.530 --> 02:21:16.210
I'm thinking, ah, literacy and
wring is exactly what we need

02:21:16.210 --> 02:21:20.120
in this situation -- the ability
to tell each other stories.

02:21:20.120 --> 02:21:22.430
So what I'm able to
tell young people back,

02:21:22.430 --> 02:21:23.730
that that's what they're missing.

02:21:23.730 --> 02:21:27.650
Their inability to articulate their
feelings comes from their inability

02:21:27.650 --> 02:21:29.190
to read, from their
inability to write.

02:21:29.190 --> 02:21:31.980
Now I'm automatically able
to spark their interest.

02:21:31.980 --> 02:21:34.900
Most of these young people have
children, have younger brothers

02:21:34.900 --> 02:21:37.840
and sisters, and they want
to be able to use their story

02:21:37.840 --> 02:21:41.060
as a positive message in
order to change the world,

02:21:41.060 --> 02:21:43.570
and so they're able to do
that once they learn how

02:21:43.570 --> 02:21:45.060
to be literate and communicate.

02:21:45.060 --> 02:21:48.050
When I use literate, I don't
completely just mean book literacy.

02:21:48.050 --> 02:21:51.180 position:56%
We definitely need multimedia,
social media literacy at this point.

02:21:51.180 --> 02:21:52.480
It's unavoidable.

02:21:52.480 --> 02:21:55.460
Most young people are getting their
news through Facebook and Twitter

02:21:55.460 --> 02:21:57.160 position:56%
and Instagram, so showing people how

02:21:57.160 --> 02:21:59.390
to navigate these things
is a very important thing.

02:21:59.390 --> 02:22:01.370
We also need musical literacy.

02:22:01.370 --> 02:22:05.800 position:56%
I have people get their
political/philosophical philosophies

02:22:05.800 --> 02:22:07.100
from rappers.

02:22:07.100 --> 02:22:08.400
They're quoting Kendrick Lamar.

02:22:08.400 --> 02:22:09.700
They're quoting J Cole.

02:22:09.700 --> 02:22:12.490
So we need to start breaking
down poetry for them.

02:22:12.490 --> 02:22:15.080
That's been my blessing
through my entire adult life.

02:22:15.080 --> 02:22:21.160
So I'm really into
practical solutions about how

02:22:21.160 --> 02:22:24.230
to affect our young people and
increase their literacy rate

02:22:24.230 --> 02:22:27.540
and to move on to the next
generation even stronger.

02:22:27.540 --> 02:22:29.740
My favorite quote is
from Jonathan B. Clark.

02:22:29.740 --> 02:22:31.760
When I was into tattoos I was
going to get it tattooed on me

02:22:31.760 --> 02:22:35.250 position:56%
but I changed my mind, so it's good.

02:22:35.250 --> 02:22:39.480
That is, "We must start projects
our grandchildren will finish."

02:22:39.480 --> 02:22:40.780
&gt;&gt; Oh, okay.

02:22:40.780 --> 02:22:44.780
&gt;&gt; Bomani Armah: He said, "There
should be a railroad across Africa.

02:22:44.780 --> 02:22:48.710
But no one man will ever live to
see it happen, so no one does it

02:22:48.710 --> 02:22:50.220
because you have to
trust your children

02:22:50.220 --> 02:22:52.070
and your children's
children to do it."

02:22:52.070 --> 02:22:53.770
That's what we have to
start talking about.

02:22:53.770 --> 02:22:55.180
That's why I'm encouraged.

02:22:55.180 --> 02:22:57.290
That's why the state of our
streets doesn't bother me

02:22:57.290 --> 02:23:00.130
because we're better than we used
to be, and we're moving forward.

02:23:00.130 --> 02:23:02.810
Dick Gregory says all the time,
"Don't let people tell you you need

02:23:02.810 --> 02:23:04.110
to go back to the old days.

02:23:04.110 --> 02:23:06.660
There is no better old
days to go back to."

02:23:06.660 --> 02:23:07.960
We're all moving forward.

02:23:07.960 --> 02:23:10.260
So these are some of the things I
want to start moving forward with.

02:23:10.260 --> 02:23:15.760
First of all, as a community we
need to start adopting our schools.

02:23:15.760 --> 02:23:18.250
They entire building,
the entire block.

02:23:18.250 --> 02:23:20.210
Everyone who lives within
a 10-block radius --

02:23:20.210 --> 02:23:21.950 position:56%
someone said something close to this
-- a 10-block radius of a school.

02:23:21.950 --> 02:23:23.250
They need to think of
that as their school.

02:23:23.250 --> 02:23:24.550
They need to be having
their events there.

02:23:24.550 --> 02:23:25.850
They need to be doing
their birthday parties

02:23:25.850 --> 02:23:27.150
and their bar mitzvahs
at that school.

02:23:27.150 --> 02:23:29.390
They need to be -- we need
to feel free that if we're

02:23:29.390 --> 02:23:31.310
in the 10-block radius of
a school, and we see some

02:23:31.310 --> 02:23:33.300
of those obviously
school-aged, we need to feel

02:23:33.300 --> 02:23:34.600
